    <article class="card">
      <div class="card-header">
        <h2 class="card-title">Rules</h2>
        <p class="card-sub">Pool rules and format for the TKE Masters Pool.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rules-wrap">
        <div class="rule-card">
          <h3>How the Pool Works</h3>
          <p>The page below is driven by the live Google Sheet feed for your pool. Participant totals update automatically from that source.</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Each participant drafts 8 golfers before the tournament begins.</li>
            <li>For each round, only the lowest 6 golfer scores count toward that participant's round total.</li>
            <li>Zero values do not count as valid round scores.</li>
            <li>The 6 counting golfers can change from round to round.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="rule-card">
          <h3>Scoring, Cut Rules, and Winning</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>If a golfer is cut, disqualified, or withdraws, penalty logic applies based on their status.</li>
            <li>Missed-cut golfers can be represented with 82s in later rounds for tracking.</li>
            <li>Round 1 through Round 4 participant scores are added together to reach the adjusted total.</li>
            <li>The leaderboard is ordered by the lowest adjusted total.</li>
            <li>The participant with the lowest final adjusted total wins the pool.</li>
          </ul>
